📌 config/initializers/saml_settings.rb

This is where SP trusts ADFS.

require 'onelogin/ruby-saml'

This loads ruby-saml classes.

## Define SAML Settings
SAML_SETTINGS = OneLogin::RubySaml::Settings.new

Creates configuration object.

🔹 SP Configuration (Your Rails App)
SAML_SETTINGS.assertion_consumer_service_url = "http://localhost:3000/saml/consume"

➡ This is where ADFS will POST SAML Response.

SAML_SETTINGS.issuer = "http://localhost:3000"

➡ Unique ID of your Rails SP.

ADFS will expect this value.


##  IdP Configuration (ADFS Details)
SAML_SETTINGS.idp_sso_target_url = "https://adfs.company.com/adfs/ls/"

➡ Where Rails redirects user for login.

SAML_SETTINGS.idp_cert = File.read(
  Rails.root.join("config", "adfs_cert.pem")
)

➡ This is ADFS public certificate
➡ Used to verify SAML signature

VERY IMPORTANT:
This is what prevents forged SAML responses.

### Security Settings

SAML_SETTINGS.name_identifier_format = "urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:1.1:nameid-format:emailAddress"

SAML_SETTINGS.authn_context ="urn:oasis:names:tc:SAML:2.0:ac:classes:PasswordProtectedTransport"

SAML_SETTINGS.security[:want_assertions_signed] = true

➡ Ensures ADFS signs assertions
➡ Prevents tampering

